enterprises.title: Cycle Salvation
enterprises.description: Cycle Salvation is a social enterprise operating under the umbrella of Causeway Work Centre. Our business strivesto achieve a triple bottom line (profit, people, planet) by providing training and employment in the field of bike mechanics to people who are economically disadvantaged, while at the same time diverting bikes destined for scrap and landfill sites.

enterprises.title: Enactus uOttawa
enterprises.description: Student-run non-profit organization that uses the power of entrepreneurial action to empower people to improve their livelihoods. Founded in 2010, the University of Ottawa team is made up of students from 7 faculties that believe that building a better world starts at home.

enterprises.title: EnviroCentre
enterprises.description: EnviroCentre is an Ottawa-based non-profit organization that helps residents, businesses and organizations conserve energy and reduce their impact on the environment, while saving money.

enterprises.title: Good Nature Groundskeeping
enterprises.description: Good Nature Groundskeeping is a social business, providing professional landscape maintenance services while also providing employment to people who are economically disadvantaged.

enterprises.title: Gourmet Express
enterprises.description: In response to clients with multiple barriers to employment and without access to the labor market, the Vanier Community Service Centre has launched the Gourmet-Xpress social enterprise, a free learning program in food preparation and customer service.

enterprises.title: Impact Hub
enterprises.description: Impact Hub Ottawa is the national capital region’s collaboration, innovation and incubation ecosystem for people and organizations working to better the world.

enterprises.title: Krackers Katering
enterprises.description: Krackers Katering is a small catering business with a big heart. At Krackers we pride ourselves on providing exceptional quality food at a reasonable price while supporting our staff in reaching their employment goals. We cater to all levels of the private and public sectors for business meetings, breakfasts, luncheons, private events and parties.

enterprises.title: Laundry Matters
enterprises.description: We provide laundry services to meet your needs; residential or commercial. Our employees are active members of the community and they take pride in their work. Our employees also have developmental disabilities. When we do your laundry, you’re helping us put a fresh spin on community.

enterprises.title: Maintenance 1a+ Workers Cooperative
enterprises.description: Maintenance 1a+ was founded in 2007 by five Colombian immigrant workers who were unsatisfied with the cleaning industry’s work conditions. Collectively, they decided to take their negative experiences and transform them into a new opportunity. The result is Maintenance 1a+, a unique workers cooperative where new immigrant workers can proudly apply their experience, and where client satisfaction, equality, and ecology are valued!  As well, Maintenance 1a+ uses only certified green cleaning products. Our co-op does its part to minimize our impact on the environment. A main goal of the co-op is to generate ongoing employment for its members. By creating a sustainable work environment that values good client relations, outstanding service, worker equality, and ecological awareness…Maintenance 1a+ is well on their way to helping make our community a greener fairer and cleaner place to do business.

enterprises.title: Market Mobile
enterprises.description: Three years ago, Ottawa’s Poverty and Hunger Working Group had a dream of creating a mobile market that would bring healthy, affordable, and culturally appropriate foods to Ottawa neighbourhoods. It seemed like a pie in the sky idea at the time. In fact, most people thought we were crazy. But this dream became a reality last summer, when, with the support of Ottawa Public Health, the Working Group secured a 40 foot OC Transpo bus to launch a 21-week pilot.

enterprises.title: National Capital Freenet
enterprises.description: The National Capital FreeNet (NCF) is an Ottawa-based, member-governed, not-for-profit alternative to commercial internet service providers.

enterprises.title: Ottawa Community Housing
enterprises.description: Ottawa Community Housing’s vision is to be a leader in providing safe and affordable homes to enable OCH tenants to fully participate in the socio-economic opportunities of the City. As a leader in the delivery of quality, affordable housing, OCH collaborates with others to develop safe and healthy communities.

enterprises.title: Ottawa Community Loan Fund
enterprises.description: The Ottawa Community Loan Fund (OCLF) is a non-profit organization providing microloans for business and professional development purposes, as well as creating awareness of the importance of a strong credit history.

enterprises.title: Ottawa Good Food Box
enterprises.description: We are a non-profit community-based initiative bringing neighbours together to buy a variety of delicious and nutritious fresh fruits and vegetables at wholesale prices. Our goal is to purchase food that is in season and is grown as close to home as possible.

enterprises.title: ReStore
enterprises.description: The ReStores’ shelves are stocked with new and gently used renovation supplies donated by homeowners and businesses. Everything is available to the public at deeply discounted prices.

enterprises.title: Right Bike
enterprises.description: Right Bike is a social business that trains and employs individuals in our community who are working to overcome barriers to employment. We deliver a community-based bike share service in Ottawa, Canada.

enterprises.title: Y's Owl Maclure
enterprises.description: Y’S OWL MACLURE CO-OPERATIVE CENTRE, in partnership with the Community, creates daytime opportunities including employment, for people with disAbilities.
